   <h2>Accounts</h2><br />
   <ul>
   <li>Accounts contain records for Dealers, OEM's, Third Party Export Partners and Vendors.</li>
   <li>Record types are assigned to each category so that fields specific to that record are displayed for user input.</li>
   <li>Account Name, Phone Number and Billing Address are required to complete setup of a new account.</li>
   <li>Dealer Accounts do not become active until the first "Closed Won" Opportunity is Paid.</li>
   <li>The system will automatically update the "Customer Created Date" field and Account Status field to Active upon the first payment.</li>
   <li>Deactivation of Dealer Accounts is managed by the Accounting Team.  When an account is deemed inactive, Accounting<br />
   will update the "Date Deactivated" field with the date the deactivation is effective.  Additionally, during the process<br />
   an account alert will be placed on the account indicating there is a cancellation in process. <a href = "/servlet/servlet.FileDownload?file=01570000001TutA">Cancellation Process</a><br /><br /></li>
   </ul>
   
   <h2>Contacts</h2><br />
   <ul>
   <li>Contacts are individuals associated with Accounts</li>
  <li>Contacts related to Active Dealer Accounts are sync'd nightly with MotoSnap User Records</li>
   <li>Contacts that have influence at multiple accounts will be listed as a single Contact on only 1 Account<br />
  and a Contact Role on additional Accounts the contact is related to</li>
   <li>New MotoSnap users sync'd as new contacts will be emailed automatically from Salesforce introducing them to our Virtual Training Offerings.</li>
   </ul><br /><br />
   
    <h2>Opportunities, Proposals, Installments, Invoices</h2><br />
   <ul>
   <li>When a new Opportunity is created against an Account, logic determines whether it’s new or existing business.</li>
<li>The Opportunity object summarizes information from the account, WebEx presentation, revenues, quote packets, activities,<br />
products, contact roles, projects, installments, campaign influence, expenses, sales team and all field history.</li>
<li>After demo, Sales determines what products or package to propose.</li>
<li>Packages and compounding products auto populate all components referred to as “child” products.</li>
<li>Child products zero out cost fields and AIS Rebates is a hard coded add.</li>
<li>Opportunity Line Item (OLI) is determined by the discount given to the opportunity multiplied by the discount <br />
associated with the package multiplied by the retail amount of the child product if purchased ala carte’.</li>  
<li>Opportunity must have all onetime fees and applicable data integration fees or it will error.</li>
<li>A click prepares an orderly PDF proposal, logic determines if discount fields are visible.</li>
<li>Sales email proposal with auto populating templates.</li>
<li>Lost Won creates an installment and locks the opportunity for management to approve the creation of the initial invoice.</li>
<li>When marked paid the project and associated project pieces fire and numerous validation rules apply</li>
   </ul>
